n Esra-Nehemia.  aThe author analyzes the different ideas of the political structure of the province of Juda which is presupposed by the book Esra-Nehemia. Three constitutional concepts and their theological outline are worked out to give insight into the development of the theological-political thoughts of post-exilic times.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aReligion and politics. 4aAltes Testament . 4aEsra (Buch) . 4aJudäa /Alte Geschichte. 4aNehemia (Buch) . 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR0 cprintz978311017055940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311085193940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110851939423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110851939/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GTRc2000d2014